Target: Ontology for representation of UK Ordnance Survey "Open Identifiers" resources.

Comment: A string for identifying objects which is unique within its namespace.
A identifier which is guaranteed to not change for the lifetime of the identified object and never be reused.
The hierarchial rank of the identifier. BLPUs and TopographicAreas of buildings are rank 0; RoadLinks are rank 1; Roads, Streets and road TopographicAreas are rank 2.
The unique string of the identifier.

The type of feature identified, which is either "blpu", "road", "roadlink", "street", or "topographicarea" (or "orroad", "orroadlink", but we do not currently import them). [OS Open Linked Identifiers Technical Specification v1.1]
The identifier type of the identifier, which also serves as its namespace; either "guid", "toid", "uprn" or "usrn". [OS Open Linked Identifiers Technical Specification v1.1]

The datetime when links for this identifier were last retrieved from the Ordnance Survey. For data from the Linked Identifiers API, this is the time of query; for Open Linked Identifiers data package downloads, this is the time of package publication.
The source from which links for this identifier were retrieved, either "api" or "package".
A relation that defines that two identifiers are linked according to the OS Open Linked Identifiers data set.
A relation that defines that an identifer identifies an identificand. For a Persistent Identifier, this property is guaranteed to not change.
